# DESIGNDOC - SyncText CRDT-Based Collaborative Text Editor# DESIGNDOC - SyncText CRDT-Based Collaborative Text Editor



## System Overview## System Architecture



SyncText is a real-time collaborative text editor that enables multiple users (3-5) to edit documents simultaneously without conflicts. It uses Conflict-Free Replicated Data Types (CRDT) with a Last-Writer-Wins (LWW) strategy for automatic conflict resolution.### High-Level Design Overview



## ArchitectureSyncText is a distributed collaborative text editing system that uses Conflict-Free Replicated Data Types (CRDT) to enable multiple users to edit documents simultaneously without locks. The system follows a peer-to-peer architecture where each user maintains their own local document copy and communicates changes to others via message queues.



