## Conclusion

SyncText demonstrates that lock-free collaborative editing is achievable using CRDT principles. The system successfully:
- Detects local changes automatically
- Broadcasts updates via message queues
- Merges concurrent edits without conflicts
- Maintains consistency across all users
- Operates without locks or mutexes

The implementation serves as a foundation for understanding distributed systems, conflict resolution, and lock-free programming paradigms.
